  "body": "I'm not sure how to contribute edits, so I'll just drop it here:\n\nThe example code under Subroutines: https://doc.perl6.org/language/functions#Subroutines has some problems and fails to compile/work\n\n1) The named character class **<-alpha-digit>** needs a space: **<-alpha -digit>**\n2) The second substitution uses **s||** where it should use matched brackets: **s[]**\n3) Neither escape sub returns a result. It modifies $_ and returns nothing and has no side-effect. Change to **S[]**\n4) The replacement in the second substitution needs to convert the matched string to the character number before invoking base: $/**.ord**.base(16)\n5) Tweaks: add needed semi, remove extra semis; single-quotes for strings\nUse **... given $str** instead of explicitly setting $_ (cleaner)\n\nMaybe this instead:\nhttps://gist.github.com/nd3i/484520fdf9543a044350818bf7fc5ef6#file-functions_sub_example-p6\n",
